						               													<description>Description from the designer:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Across the ages, the most terrifying Mexican legends have been kept within the pages of the ancestral book: TerroriXico&amp;#10;When the book is opened, the monsters within it are released. A team of bold hunters must chase them down and return the monsters to their pages before they wreak havoc&amp;#10;In this semi-cooperative card game, players must help each other in order to capture the monsters.&amp;#10;By using ancestral relics and other special cards, they will prove their courage and defeat the monsters, earning victory points.&amp;#10;The player with the most victory points win, for proving to be the bravest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;TerririXico is a cooperative card game about myths and Mexican legends, where as a team we must return the monsters to the book.&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All players have a deck of 50 cards, 4 kind of relics and special cards.&amp;#10;Every monster battle is a round. By turns players can play 2 cards in the battle zone, 1 open card and 1 face down, or 2 open cards applying the effects of the cards if it has.&amp;#10;The player who plays in total more relics, will win the round and take the firts place and the monster card, the other players gains the points from second place.&amp;#10;If any player passes by can not play cards receive 1 card of trauma,these trauma cards go to the player's deck.&amp;#10;But this battle might have consequences in the minds of the players; if they can't play any card to stay in the battle, they will receive trauma cards, If no player can't play anything they might also receive friendly fire&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Open the book and let the monster hunt begin!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
